ds.  In other words high end guilds would not have to sweep up the lower end boss mobs (Rhag2 and THO for example) in order to satisfy their caster ranks, and conversely lower and mid range guilds would not have suffer because they are unable to either a) have access to a given boss mob because uberguild_01 is actively trying to sweep up copies of &lt;insert your Luclin uber spell here&gt;.. or b) actually even seriously consider attempting something like Cursed or High Priest, lets face it those mobs ( and others that fit this category ) are just completely out of reach of many guilds, and always will be.</P><P>Now, you may say that perhaps those at VI never intended for any but the most elite of wizards to obtain Garrison's, and therefore nobody but the most elite of guilds should be able to obtain it for them.  For that one spell, perhaps the argument could hold.  It is an incredibly powerful spell, that is not hampered by any stacking restrictions.  But for the others, Funeral Pyre included, it is just rediculous the way they are entering the world at this time.</P><P>Now, as far as gDMF and Gangrenous Touch.. novelty spells. Nothing more than convenience and novelty.  Personally i want them and if i ever feel that i want them badly enough all i have to do is go to Chardok and camp the damn things. Simple as that. Hell, i am pretty sure that with enough practice and patience, i could find a way to solo the Korocust room. If any changes were to be made to these spells, the only ones that make any sense would be to possibly up the drop rate a hair, or make gDMF researchable.</P><P>&lt;Necro_01&gt;Look at me, I am lifetapping a mob that is immune to magic. &lt;Necro_02&gt;Yay for you, quit wasting mana and use your fire dots.</P><P>Vtyn<BR>Warlock<BR>Heaven and Earth</P><P> </font></td>
